   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422595_1825_05_05_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Black-Castle_IE">Black Castle</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Navan_IE">Navan</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <note>Maria Edgeworth</note>
                  <date when="1825-05-05">May 5<hi rend="supercript">th</hi>, 1825.</date></dateline>
               <lb/>
               <salute>
                  Dear Sir,<lb/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               I will take up only 3 minutes<lb/>
               of your time - If you can<lb/>
               will you procure for me a<lb/>
               copy of the principal evidence<lb/>
               on Irish <add>Cat-</add> affairs before the H of<lb/>
               Commons &amp; Lords - I <choice>
                  <orig>under<lb/>
                  stand</orig>
                  <reg>understand</reg>
               </choice> that duplicates can be<lb/>
               had by <hi rend="underline">great</hi> members of<lb/>
               parliament like you - These<lb/>
               reports are most valuable -<lb/>
               -<hi rend="underline">I admire M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography#BlakV1">Blakes</persName> evidence<lb/>
               particularly</hi> - <del>and</del>
               <persName ref="./Personography#LewiF1">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Frank<lb/>
                  land</orig>
                     <reg>Frankland</reg>
                  </choice> Lewis</persName>'s contains much<lb/>
               excellent information - So does<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography#FostJ1">Leslie Fosters</persName> - <persName ref="./Personography#DoylX1">Doyle</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography#OConX1">O'Connor</persName>
               <lb/>
               admirable in their different ways<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>- How I shall enjoy hearing you<lb/>
               talk over all this some time at<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName> - I tremble for<lb/>
               the consequences of the D of Y's <choice>
                  <orig>declara<lb/>
                     <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422595_1825_05_05_page02.jpg"/>
            
               tion</orig>
                  <reg>declaration</reg>
               </choice> - write one line to me to<lb/>
               tell me whether you tremble<lb/>
               or can still write your name<lb/>
               in <hi rend="underline">steady characters</hi>
            </p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>
               Y<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. truly
                  <persName ref="./Personography#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>Direct to me Black Castle<lb/>
               Navan - <lb/>
               </p>
               <p>
               I have heard much of you<lb/>
               from various English friends<lb/>
               of late but nothing from you<lb/>
               </p>
               <p>How did you like Bowood<lb/>
               </p>
               <p>When will you come to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths<lb/>
               Town</placeName> - arrange <hi rend="underline">that</hi> between<lb/>
               the fits of politics &amp; let me<lb/>
               know before I am quite<lb/>
               out of patience with your delays<lb/>
               </p>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422595_1825_05_05_page03.jpg"/>
               <p>
               I trust that the <persName ref="./Personography#PeryT1">Empress<lb/>
            Theodosia</persName> is in our<lb/>
            interests - I will promise<lb/>
            her a bribe of a little book<lb/>
            for her children by &amp; by<lb/>
            &amp; soon too if she makes you<lb/>
            answer this as I wish or<lb/>
            if she writes one line herself<lb/>
            giving me reason to believe<lb/>
            we shall really have you<lb/>
            at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName> as<lb/>
            soon as you are free<lb/>
               </p>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422595_1825_05_05_page04.jpg"/>
               <p>
                  <note>
                     <persName ref="./Personography#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
                  </note>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
